# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# CAM-PULSE Environment Configuration
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Copy this file:  cp .env.example .env
# Fill in your keys and model choices below, then run:  cam setup
#
# cam setup reads this file — no need to re-enter keys or models.
# It will only ask about budgets and mission profile.
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# ── API Keys ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Required for PULSE (X-Scout discovery via Grok)
# Get your key at https://console.x.ai/
XAI_API_KEY=your-xai-api-key-here

# Required for multi-agent LLM routing (all 4 agents go through this)
# Get your key at https://openrouter.ai/keys
OPENROUTER_API_KEY=your-openrouter-key-here

# Required for embeddings (novelty scoring)
# Get your key at https://aistudio.google.com/apikey
GOOGLE_API_KEY=your-google-api-key-here

# Optional: per-provider keys (only if NOT using OpenRouter for that agent)
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=your-anthropic-key-here
# OPENAI_API_KEY=your-openai-key-here

# ── CAM-SEQ Security Lane (Optional) ──────────────────────────────────
# Default new-user path:
# - use Docker for Semgrep
# - keep CodeQL deferred unless you have a managed/advanced setup
#
# Repo-local Semgrep config is available at security/semgrep.yml.
# If Docker is installed and running, this avoids local Semgrep setup.
CLAW_SECURITY_USE_DOCKER=1
CLAW_FEATURE_COMPONENT_CARDS=1
CLAW_FEATURE_APPLICATION_PACKETS=1
CLAW_FEATURE_CONNECTOME_SEQ=1
CLAW_FEATURE_CRITICAL_SLOT_POLICY=1
CLAW_FEATURE_A2A_PACKETS=1
# CLAW_SEMGREP_CONFIG=/absolute/path/to/semgrep.yml
#
# Advanced / managed mode only:
# CLAW_CODEQL_DATABASE=/absolute/path/to/codeql-db
# CLAW_CODEQL_QUERIES=/absolute/path/to/python-security-and-quality.qls

# ── Models ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Browse models at https://openrouter.ai/models (sort by price/quality)
# Format: provider/model-name (OpenRouter routing format)
#
# These are the 4 CAM agent slots. Pick any model for each.
# Leave blank or commented to disable that agent.

# Agent: claude — used for analysis, documentation, complex reasoning
CAM_MODEL_CLAUDE=anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-6

# Agent: codex — used for refactoring, bulk tests, code generation
CAM_MODEL_CODEX=openai/gpt-4.1-mini

# Agent: gemini — used for dependency analysis, full repo comprehension
CAM_MODEL_GEMINI=google/gemini-2.5-flash

# Agent: grok — used for quick fixes, web lookup
CAM_MODEL_GROK=x-ai/grok-4-1-fast-non-reasoning

# PULSE X-Scout model (must be grok-4 family for x_search support)
CAM_PULSE_MODEL=grok-4-1-fast-non-reasoning
